
= platform dedicated to the research, documentation, and circulation of network culture theory. Its main study and documentation areas are the processes of social and cultural inclusion of telecommunication networks and their effects in the development of new artistic practices and critical knowledge production.

Inclusiva-net eBooks via http://medialab-prado.es/article/inclusiva-net_e-books


=Description=

Since 2007 four international meetings have been celebrated with lectures and paper presentations selected by international open calls. These e-book gather, in English and Spanish, all the theoretical documentation generated during the meetings. 


=Examples=

 
* 4º Inclusiva-net Meeting: P2P Networks and Processes, Madrid, July, 2009


* 3er Inclusiva-net Meeting: Net.art (second epoch). The Evolution of Artistic Creation in the Net-system. Buenos Aires, Argentina, March 2009


* 2º Inclusiva-net Meeting: Digital Networks and Physical Space. Madrid, March 2008 


* 1er Inclusiva-net Meeting: New Art Dynamics in Web 2 mode


